					<description><![CDATA[<p>Rylo Raises $85M to Scale AI Communication Platform Rylo has raised $85 million in new funding. The round was led by General Catalyst’s Customer Value Fund. Canaan also led new</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/rylo-raises-85m-ai-accessibility-funding/" data-wpel-link="internal">Rylo Raises $85M Series Growth Funding as AI Accessibility Demand Surges</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Rylo Raises $85M to Scale AI Communication Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rylo has raised $85 million in new funding. The round was led by General Catalyst’s Customer Value Fund. Canaan also led new investment participation. Existing investors Vertex Ventures and Contour joined the round. The funding brings total capital raised above $100 million.  The company was previously known as Nagish. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It has now been rebranded as Rylo. The company builds AI communication tools for the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community. It focuses on real-time accessibility solutions.  It aims to improve communication in daily life and workplaces.  Rylo operates from Tel Aviv and New York. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It plans to expand engineering and product development teams. The company will also scale commercial operations. The funding supports broader product expansion. It also strengthens long-term infrastructure development. Investors see strong demand in accessibility technology.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Platform Expands Real-Time Communication Tools</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rylo builds an AI-powered communication platform. It delivers real-time captioning for phone calls. It also supports in-person transcription. The system converts speech into text instantly. It also enables text-to-speech responses. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It improves accessibility in personal and professional settings. The platform includes AI features for communication context. These include sentiment analysis and speaker recognition. It also includes fraud detection tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rylo Sign supports real-time sign language translation. It was developed after the acquisition of Sign.mt in 2025. The system translates between spoken and signed languages. The platform is designed for everyday communication. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It helps users navigate work meetings and public interactions.  It reduces dependency on third-party interpretation services. The company builds tools around real user feedback. It focuses on reliability and accuracy in communication. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It aims to create a seamless user experience. The system supports multiple communication channels. It is designed to improve independence for users. It also enhances accessibility in high-pressure environments.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investor Confidence Builds Around Accessibility AI<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202698" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202698" class="size-full wp-image-202698" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/a-vibrant-futuristic-poster-showcases-an_WT17KZePU4ahqw860bNc3Q_uXT5Zn_IQsWHB-CucWO5MA.png" alt="AI-powered accessibility platform enabling real-time speech-to-text and sign language translation." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202698" class="wp-caption-text">Rylo gains investor confidence as AI transforms accessibility and real-time communication systems. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">General Catalyst led the growth investment through its Customer Value Fund. Canaan also supported the round. Vertex Ventures and Contour participated as existing investors. “Rylo has built a product that clearly resonates with users,” said Andrew Ziperski, Partner at General Catalyst. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He highlighted strong product-market fit. He noted the company addresses a long underserved market. He said AI enables scalable accessibility solutions. Investors view Rylo as part of a wider AI accessibility shift. The sector has historically lacked large-scale innovation. AI is changing cost and delivery models.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company sits within a growing assistive technology category. It targets real-world communication barriers. It focuses on enterprise and consumer adoption. Rylo’s model reflects broader AI infrastructure trends. It uses automation to reduce dependency on human intermediaries. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It increases communication speed and reliability. The market opportunity spans millions of users globally. Demand is driven by accessibility regulation and digital communication growth. Investors expect continued expansion in this sector.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/golden-analytics-14m-seed-extension/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Golden Analytics Raises $14M Seed Extension as AI Analytics Demand Surges</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Plans and Product Ecosystem Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rylo plans to expand its engineering and operations teams. It will invest in product development and infrastructure scaling. It also plans to strengthen AI research capabilities. The company has already grown through acquisition strategy. It acquired Sign.mt to build Rylo Sign. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform improves sign language translation capabilities. Rylo aims to expand beyond captioning tools. It plans a wider suite of AI communication features. These include workplace accessibility tools and fraud detection systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company targets both individual and enterprise users. It focuses on scalable communication solutions. It aims to serve the estimated 48 million Americans with hearing loss. Rylo’s leadership believes accessibility should be universal. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform is designed for real-time reliability. It prioritises privacy and regulatory compliance. The company continues to refine AI models based on usage data. It focuses on improving accuracy and </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/responsiveness" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">responsiveness</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. It aims to reduce communication friction across environments. Rylo’s long-term strategy includes global expansion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It plans to scale adoption across multiple markets. It continues to position itself as a core accessibility infrastructure provider. Rylo advances an AI accessibility platform enabling real-time communication for Deaf and hard-of-hearing users.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/rylo-raises-85m-ai-accessibility-funding/" data-wpel-link="internal">Rylo Raises $85M Series Growth Funding as AI Accessibility Demand Surges</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
