					<description><![CDATA[<p>Morpho has successfully closed a $175 million funding round. The strategic capital injection values the Ethereum-based protocol at up to $2 billion, representing one of the largest fundraising events in</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/morpho-raises-175-million-to-expand-defi-lending/" data-wpel-link="internal">Morpho Raises $175 Million to Expand DeFi Lending</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://morpho.org/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Morpho </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has successfully closed a $175 million </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/syntheticfi-raises-13m-surpasses-2b-in-assets/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The strategic capital injection values the Ethereum-based protocol at up to $2 billion, representing one of the largest fundraising events in DeFi history and another sign of significant institutional interest in on-chain credit markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The heavily subscribed round was led by the best-in-class triad of elite VC investors. The fundraiser was co-led by three of the most reputable VC funds in the crypto space, i.e., Paradigm, a16z Crypto and Ribbit Capital. The round also saw participation from some of the biggest crypto-native venture capital funds and traditional asset management giants such as Apollo Funds, Circle Ventures, VanEck, Variant, Wintermute Ventures, Ledger Cathay, HashKey Capital, Mirana Ventures, and many more.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to company disclosures, the investment was structured as a native cryptocurrency token purchase based on the token&#8217;s average monthly pricing, bringing Morpho&#8217;s total cumulative funding to $244.35 million since its inception.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Rewriting the Rules of Decentralized Lending</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2021 by French entrepreneur Paul Frambot alongside co-founders Merlin Egalite, Julien Thomas, and Mathis Gontier Delaunay, Morpho originally gained prominence for its &#8220;Morpho Optimiser&#8221;. This initial protocol acted as a peer-to-peer efficiency layer sitting directly on top of legacy giants Aave and Compound, matching lenders and borrowers directly to squeeze out better interest rates.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, Morpho has since evolved into a highly distinct, modular lending infrastructure. Unlike traditional DeFi protocols that rely on centralised governance to set risk parameters, collateral ratios, and asset tiers for the entire user base, Morpho allows anyone to launch their own independent, highly customised lending markets.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202695" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202695" class="size-large wp-image-202695" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Trading-chart-1024x683.jpg" alt="Trading chart" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-202695" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By separating the core, immutable lending engine from the risk management layer, third-party entities can curate independent financial vaults with customised risk-reward profiles. This architectural shift has allowed Morpho to capture a staggering $6.6 billion in Total Value Locked (TVL) and cross $11 billion in total deposits, positioning it as the second-largest decentralised lending infrastructure in the ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;I think traditional finance is going to have to wear shorts,&#8221; noted 25-year-old CEO Paul Frambot in an interview with </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">Fortune</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400">, lightheartedly referencing the cultural convergence between suit-and-tie institutional giants and hoodie-wearing Web3 developers. &#8220;The financial industry is realising that open, modular credit networks are inherently more efficient, transparent, and resilient than legacy banking stacks.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/syntheticfi-raises-13m-surpasses-2b-in-assets/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">SyntheticFi Raises $13M, Surpasses $2B in Assets</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Crossover Asset for Major Crypto Exchanges</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Morpho&#8217;s institutional-first design has already triggered massive adoption among major centralised financial firms looking to offer non-custodial yields to their retail and institutional clients. Cryptographic infrastructure giants and global exchanges, including Coinbase, Binance, Kraken, Bitwise, Galaxy Digital, and Anchorage Digital, have all actively integrated into Morpho&#8217;s universal lending network.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By plugging into Morpho&#8217;s open-source API, exchanges can instantly route their users&#8217; stablecoin assets into curated yield vaults (such as those managed by specialised firms like Gauntlet or Steakhouse Financial) without having to build, manage, or underwrite their own complex lending books. This setup allows platforms like Binance and Coinbase to tap into a massive, aggregate global liquidity pool seamlessly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Morpho is transforming decentralised lending from an isolated, crypto-native experiment into a foundational layer of global financial infrastructure,&#8221; said Guy Wuollet, general partner at a16z crypto. &#8220;Their modular design allows regulated financial institutions to engage safely with on-chain capital markets while strictly maintaining their unique compliance and risk requirements.&#8221;</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Horizon: Institutional Scalability</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $175 million in fresh capital will be heavily weaponised to scale Morpho&#8217;s open credit network globally. The organisation plans to accelerate its engineering roadmap, deepen its integration pipeline across EVM-compatible (Ethereum Virtual Machine) layer-2 chains, and aggressively fund global ecosystem development.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Furthermore, a significant portion of the funds will be used to build out compliance tooling and developer kits specifically tailored for institutional asset managers. As legacy capital allocators increasingly seek to tokenise real-world assets (RWAs) such as private credit, Treasury bills, and commercial paper, Morpho aims to position its modular vaults as the primary marketplace where those tokenised assets can be cleanly put to work as collateral for institutional borrowing.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/morpho-raises-175-million-to-expand-defi-lending/" data-wpel-link="internal">Morpho Raises $175 Million to Expand DeFi Lending</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
