		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=202673</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>CeQur has successfully raised a $100 million Series E financing round to take the company into a period of significant commercial expansion, increasing access to its injection-free wearable insulin delivery</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cequr-raises-100m-to-expand-diabetes-care/" data-wpel-link="internal">CeQur Raises $100M to Expand Diabetes Care</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://myceqursimplicity.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">CeQur </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has successfully raised a $100 million Series E </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/beacon-software-raises-225m-series-c-for-ai-roll-up/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round to take the company into a period of significant commercial expansion, increasing access to its injection-free wearable insulin delivery device for people with diabetes. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">The round highlights investors&#8217; enduring faith in CeQur&#8217;s results and commercial prospects to build its manufacturing base. </span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Simplifying the Mealtime Insulin Burden</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Established to address the daily inconveniences of managing diabetes, CeQur has identified adherence to mealtime (bolus) insulin therapy as a critical problem in healthcare. For the millions of insulin users taking multiple daily injections, carrying insulin pens around, managing fine syringes and delivering large, visible injections is an enormous mental and physical pain.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s primary solution is CeQur Simplicity, a waterproof, ultra-discreet, wearable patch designed to be worn under clothes. The hardware entirely replaces the need for traditional mealtime injections. To administer a dose, users simply squeeze two mechanical buttons on the side of the device through their clothing</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The hardware entirely replaces the need for traditional mealtime injections. To administer a dose, users simply squeeze two mechanical buttons on the side of the device through their clothing. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">Historically, each device could hold up to 200 units of rapid-acting insulin and replace an average of 12 injections over a four-day period by delivering bolus doses in two-unit increments. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_202686" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202686" class="size-large wp-image-202686" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/blood-sugar-device-1024x683.jpg" alt="blood sugar device" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-202686" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, this huge injection of fresh capital comes at a time when the platform&#8217;s clinical utility is expanding rapidly. CeQur has received important new guarantees from the FDA that extend the device&#8217;s features from a seven-day wear time and one or two-unit dosing to a seven-day wear time and one or two-unit dosing.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We have the commercial infrastructure, new clinical evidence, and an exciting pipeline,&#8221; said Bradley Paddock, President and CEO of CeQur, in a statement accompanying the announcement. &#8220;Now we have the capital to accelerate our growth. CeQur Simplicity is ready to reach every patient and physician who wants to simplify their insulin delivery and improve their diabetes management.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/beacon-software-raises-225m-series-c-for-ai-roll-up/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Beacon Software Raises $225M Series C for AI Roll-Up</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Commercial Momentum and Insurance Integration</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $100 million Series E will directly support a rapid scaling of CeQur’s domestic and international field sales teams, deepening partnerships with endocrinologists and diabetes care specialists. </span>Strong financial performance and high medical insurance reimbursement rates heavily back this commercial push. Company data shows standard pharmacy benefits cover more than 85% of all insurance claims for the device, rather than complex DME channels.</p>
<p>This streamlined pharmacy access allows patients to secure the wearable patch at an average co-pay of less than $45 per month, substantially lowering the financial barriers to advanced diabetes tech. <span style="font-weight: 400">The strong manufacturing capabilities also support market demand. CeQur had already finalised validations for its high-volume, 40,000 sq. ft automated cleanroom manufacturing plant, which will provide this global commercial demand with no supply obstacles.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strong Clinical Validation</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond commercial convenience, CeQur’s expansion is anchored by compelling real-world medical data. Clinical studies evaluate that nearly 90% of patients reported adhering to their prescribed insulin regimens significantly better when transitioning to the patch compared to multiple daily needle injections.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Furthermore, patients utilising the wearable platform achieved markedly improved A1C levels (a metric tracking long-term blood sugar levels) and spent significantly more &#8220;time-in-range&#8221;, reducing the long-term health risks associated with glycaemic spikes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;This financing is a direct reflection of what the CeQur team has built and the confidence our investors have placed in our growth trajectory,&#8221; added Mike Rubino, Chief Financial Officer of CeQur. &#8220;We are committed to deploying this capital to deliver on the full potential of CeQur Simplicity for patients, providers, and healthcare systems worldwide.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cequr-raises-100m-to-expand-diabetes-care/" data-wpel-link="internal">CeQur Raises $100M to Expand Diabetes Care</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
