					<description><![CDATA[<p>SyntheticFi has raised $13 million in venture financing while simultaneously breaching a major operational milestone, surpassing $2 billion in regulatory assets under management (RAUM). The new capital structure and asset</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/syntheticfi-raises-13m-surpasses-2b-in-assets/" data-wpel-link="internal">SyntheticFi Raises $13M, Surpasses $2B in Assets</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.syntheticfi.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">SyntheticFi </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised $13 million in venture </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/beacon-software-raises-225m-series-c-for-ai-roll-up/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">while simultaneously breaching a major operational milestone, surpassing $2 billion in regulatory assets under management (RAUM). The new capital structure and asset growth numbers mark a fundamental transformation in how independent financial advisors are handling client liabilities and liquidity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The large-scale venture round received support from a widely respected syndicate of institutional investors from the fintech and wealth management landscapes. The round was supported by Y Combinator, Social Leverage, NextGen VP (Brown Advisory subsidiary), and The Compound Capital Fund. The funding will directly back the expansion of SyntheticFi’s engineering team and fund a broader rollout of its proprietary liabilities-planning software.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Democratizing Institutional Box Spreads</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2023 by a team of quantitative developers and finance specialists, including CEO Tony Yang, San Francisco-based SyntheticFi caught the wealth-tech sector&#8217;s attention by taking a highly sophisticated institutional options trading strategy and wrapping it inside an accessible, compliance-ready software layer for Registered Investment Advisors (RIAs).</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Historically, if a wealthy individual required a large cash injection, say a down payment on an expensive property, for an expansion to their business or to cover an unexpected tax bill, then they could either sell some of their investments and incur huge capital gains tax or take out a high-rate margin loan or Securities-Backed Line of Credit (SBLOC) from a traditional legacy bank.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202655" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202655" class="size-full wp-image-202655" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/SyntheticFi-Logo.jpg" alt="SyntheticFi Logo" width="480" height="300" /><p id="caption-attachment-202655" class="wp-caption-text">Source: SyntheticFi</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SyntheticFi introduces a third, vastly cheaper alternative through automated box spread options financing. A box spread is an options strategy combining four European-style options (specifically on the liquid S&amp;P 500 Index) to borrow cash at near-wholesale market rates, effectively tracking the Secured Overnight Financing Rate (SOFR).</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Because these trades are cleared through public options exchanges rather than a centralised bank balance sheet, the typical financial intermediary markups are entirely eliminated. While traditional bank broker-dealers frequently charge 7% to 10%+ on margin lines, SyntheticFi enables advisors to construct floating or fixed-rate portfolio loans starting near 4.05% to 5.30%. Furthermore, because the structure utilises options contracts, the underlying loan interest can often be classified as a tax write-off against investment income, completely independent of the loan’s eventual destination.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/beacon-software-raises-225m-series-c-for-ai-roll-up/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Beacon Software Raises $225M Series C for AI Roll-Up</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling Across the RIA Landscape</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s growth metrics reflect an immediate market pull. Since the start of 2026, SyntheticFi has roughly tripled its platform scale, now supporting more than 300 independent advisory firms representing a network of 3,000+ individual financial advisors across the United States.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform’s growth is heavily tied to its frictionless, &#8220;asset-light&#8221; integration structure. Unlike legacy private banks that require high-net-worth clients to physically transfer their multi-million dollar portfolios to a new institution to secure a low lending rate, SyntheticFi functions entirely as a tech-enabled sub-advisor. It hooks natively into an advisor&#8217;s existing custody accounts at major institutions, including Charles Schwab, Fidelity, Pershing, and Interactive Brokers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;For a long time, borrowing was treated as an isolated, transactional conversation separate from holistic wealth management,&#8221; stated Tony Yang, co-founder and CEO of SyntheticFi. &#8220;That is fundamentally changing. Advisors are increasingly expected to optimise their clients&#8217; entire balance sheets, both assets and liabilities. The rapid expansion we are experiencing reflects an urgent demand from modern firms for sophisticated, low-cost debt management tools that create tangible alpha for their client bases.&#8221;</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Next Steps: Expanding the Automated Lending Suite</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $13 million capital injection arrives as SyntheticFi expands its specialised product vertical. The startup has begun heavily marketing its &#8220;Hybrid Mortgage&#8221; programme to independent real estate teams and financial planning networks. This strategy blends elements of traditional real estate mortgages with automated securities-backed loans, allowing affluent clients to execute home purchases with $0 cash out of pocket while keeping their equity portfolios fully invested in the market to capture compound returns.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With $2 billion in RAUM locked into its system, SyntheticFi plans to focus its newly expanded engineering workforce on automated rollover tools and risk-monitoring dashboards, protecting RIAs from abrupt margin call hazards during periods of heightened market volatility.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/syntheticfi-raises-13m-surpasses-2b-in-assets/" data-wpel-link="internal">SyntheticFi Raises $13M, Surpasses $2B in Assets</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
